colonial experience
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the practical experience of life in colonial New Zealand to be gained by new immigrants; the conventional wisdom of an old hand.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
